    "2846603305154122007/03/31 23:27:32LordThurisazThe staff gets you 2g, 16s and 13c.  The shoulders get you 91s and 95c.  So you break 3g even before counting the 65s reward.  Nearly 4g total (3g 73s and 08c).  Very good amount of money for an easy quest.",
    "2846182268211753542007/11/11 06:12:44belfonzusThe shadowbolt volley will hit the whole party, but you can get out of line of sight.  I pulled agro and hid around the corner to get her to come to me, but she cast the volley first.  I was the only one that didn't take the hit, cos of where I was hiding.",
    "2846541214054122006/12/03 01:44:23OrmrissHydromancer Velratha is in the same room as Gahz'rilla.  She patrols near the pool in the middle of the room.  Take out the other patrols first as they pass the south end of the pool.  Once they are all gone, clear the static mobs down one side of the room, working your way north to the area Velratha patrols.\
\
Velratha is not much more difficult than the other magic users in Zul'Farrak.  Her only edge is the ability to use a totem called \"Wrath of Zum'rah\" which summons skeletons.  You can counter this by assigning someone with fast attack speed to watch for totems, and have them attack the totem as soon as it appears.  However, it is possible to do enough damage to Velratha that she will wind up focusing on healing herself, thus never casting the totem.\
\
BTW druids, shamans, rogues and hunters should not pass up this quest even though the rewards are useless to them.  You get both of the items and 65s.  Selling both items should yield well over 2g, bringing the monetary reward close to 3g.",
