    "661050897361386902007/03/14 05:13:48JosinaAfter the release of Burning Crusade and the opening of Caverns of Time, the Alterac Swiss can now be found at a vendor in there. He stands in a tower, right before you enter the big room.",
    "6610136410101364102007/08/12 10:24:50VaidemineSome of the best drop rates for the Giant Eggs are off the various 'Screechers' in Felwood.  If you go there to get your eggs, be sure to get the Monster Omelet (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=16110) recipe from your factions' rep while in Felwood.  It is available at Lv225 Cooking, and is a recipe calling for Giant Eggs.  Might as well grab a few extra while you're farming.",
    "6610386901020386902007/02/19 11:59:31BinaryBurnoutAt the time of completing this quest I was a level 50 warrior. After minor deliberations concerning time and level efficiency, I determined the following mobs and path was best for someone of the mentioned level to complete this quest...\
\
|-- Giant Egg --|\
• Primitive/Savage Owlbeasts of the Hinterlands\
-- Average of a 33.5% drop rate\
-- http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=2928 || http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=2929\
\
