    "2882133295301332952007/08/06 15:18:24LuckybucketFun quest with decent rewards, but rather annoying. Overall, it's worth it. Used 2 maps in one trip and walked away with 4 decent greens and some vendor trash. The pirates that come out to protect don't drop that bad either, at least another 10s or so.\
\
There are two locations in which I found with the Landmark: one at 50,90 and another at 54,95. I used 54, 95 and only encountered 50,90 when searching the area after completing the quest, so I cannot confirm whether it can be used or not, but it looks identical to the other.\
\
Anyways, when tackling this quest, find the landmark and search it. As far as I know the only way to reach it is swimming and walking on the shore to the east of the mountain range. When you search the landmark, 5 pirates will come out in a pattern somewhat like an \"S\". If you have AoE skills, take them out quick and easy. If you don't, such as a Rogue, take out the corners to kill them with 3 on 1 and 2 on 1 fights. Not too difficult. Most threatening thing is a turtle joining the fight, so take care of them beforehand.\
\
Once you kill them, get a key and open the chest. You should get about 2 green items, with a chance at some rares, and a total of 5-6 items, so have some space ready or open it once your in town to vendor off some stuff.\
\
This place is a pain to reach, so I suggest having some method of teleporting out, such as a Hearthstone, to avoid making the trip twice: once in and once out. If you die, then that's yet another trip, so be cautious and don't take any risks.",
