  ["Imp Delivery60"] = {
    "762960npcGorzeeki Wildeyes14437npcGorzeeki Wildeyes14437660017623276243762547629",
    "7629182016501820162007/11/10 15:29:12WukedThis is a very useful guide for all 70 Warlocks. I followed it myself as an affliction Warlock and it went smoothly.\
\
From thottbot, written by Shahwigs\
\
SOLO: 70 Demo lock, regular BC drop/quest gear.\
\
1) Have the key to scholo...\
2) Bring at least 10 shards, I did it with 5.\
3) Curse on Weakness is your BEST friend here.\
4) Enter scholo, 4 dead skelly warriors on the entry bridge. Single pull right and left front statics with Curse of Weakness. Dont send pet or you get ALL 4. The 2 in the back you will get together so just CoW them, throw some dots, tap tank, and HEAL Felguard. It's really not hard at 70 it seems, or CoW is just really awesome.\
5)Open the door and pull the roaming skell warrior you see. Go in room, go down to the right side corner and pull the roamers to here as they walk by. You can clear the close statics if you want. Go left across the room and through the other gate. I pulled the right statics next to the door, 3 mobs, but probably didnt have too as the other side didnt aggro when I went through door.\
6) Go in and turn left and you will see a long hall with 3 roamers and static bad guys on each side. You can ignore the statics and actually kill the roamers in the middle of the room without aggroing them. Go to the end of the room and open the gate.\
\
7) 4 roamers in this next room and 2 come close enough to the door to pull them outside the room 1 at a time. when this is done, go in and turn left.Straight across this room is where your going, but you have 2 roamers left, further into this room. stay in the middle of the hall and pull the first roamer to you and kill it all quite like in the middle of the hall. Careful not to aggro the statics on both sides.. The three static mobs in the center of the room can be completely avoided. Run across middle of the room, timing roamer on the other side, and pull him from the other doorway.\
\
8) Go through the door to the bird room, Aviary I think, and hug the left wall to the other end, you WILL aggro the far birdguy next to the steps down. Kill that set and go downstars to just outside Rattlegores room.\
\
9) Rattlegore is in the center of this room on a pile of bones. The 4 mobs, 2 in front 2 in back, are chained to him.I knew that from this board, but THIS is where I WIPED because I underestimated the these due the easiness of everything else I was owning. Pull the front 2 one at a time with CoW. In this fight you are a priest. Keep CoW on the mobs at all times, start tap tanking / healing pet EARLY, its like they have a dmg multiplier or something. Inch up toward the middle right and pull the right back one when it paths close. When it's dead, run around to the right of rattlegore and behind him on the back wall and pull the last one. Rattlegore himself is a bit harder than them in the fact that he stuns your pet and goes for you. stay back off him and do him like you did his minions. I ended up back at the door to his room with him when he finally droped. GET THE KEY to the Viewing Room.\
\
10) Go back to the first room you came in at, killing any roamers that repopped, I had one. Go to the exit and turn the direction you came in.Go accross the bridge on the right side and sac your pet. Jump down off the bridge to the far right corner, next to the Viewing Room door, and make a pet as fast as you can. A Glowing goul thingy will aggro and 2 non elite skellies will add.. Get them dead and open the viewing room door.\
\
11) Go in, All NON aggro, DONT talk to any of them, run accross the room to the next gate. Open it and go into the hall.\
\
12) You are now outside the lab, walk just inside the room and kill the 3 statics to the right, next to the alchemy table your going to use.\
\
13) Release Imp and let him do his imp thing. Imp Delivery Completed!",
    "7629210486102104862007/12/31 12:54:29warhowlthis is how i did it( NOTE: leave the lock at the entrance and only go with druid)\
1.get a friend to help (recomended a feral druid)\
2. kill the first 4 guards( bear form and use Demoralizing Roar ALOT as it will help reduce dmg takes by almost 20%)\
3.prowl to the first iron gate to you left as you enter the next room.\
4 from there on prowl to the stairs before the door to Rattlegore\
5. now Rattlegore has 2 npc in front of him you need to kill before you can get to him.\
6. kill the 2 trash in front of him and then kill him also( he actualy hits alot less then the trash around him just stay near wall as he will ocasionaly throw you)\
7. when he dies loot the Viewing Room Key and then prowl back all the way up.\
8 now at the room where you killed the first 4 skeltal guards you should be able to jump down as druid and kill the first group near the door and then get your lock down and go trough the door.\
9. keep walking as the next room is all neutral to you and go on to the next hall then room.\
10. in there kill the 4 trash groups( no need to kill the boss) and then release the imp todo his job and then your done\
\
took me around 30 tops to complete all of this with a lvl 70 feral druid and my lvl 62 lock\
\
Good luck( PS: you wil still need a healer/dps for dire maul",
    "7629911316091132006/12/07 17:42:35RodeorThis quest is really quite simple for the warlock dreadsteed quest line. After you had completed the pre requisite quests for this quest, you must goto Scholomance's alchemy lab. This lab looks like any ordinary lab and it is in the same room as raz frostweaver(lich boss). You can either let the imp loose before killing the boss, or after, it does not matter.",
    "76291149821101149822007/07/03 12:27:06CleodoraOnce the imp is done and you get the completion message, don't be worried if you see the special paper nowhere in your inventory. It's not supposed to be there, J'eevee has it with him *inside the jar*, so you're done, no extra quest item to haul around aside from the jar itself.",
    "762941593110415932007/02/24 13:08:21PowerstreamNote that you wont be able to do the quest in the shattrah alchemy lab.",
    "7629127197301271972007/07/26 14:00:25Protagonistsoloed at 70 in just under an hour.\
you only really need to kill pats everything else can be avoided as long as you're carefull.\
use a VW to tank rattlegore, he actually dosn't hit as hard as the other mobs in his room, he has a temporary aggro reset though which is kind of annoying.\
after you get the key backtrack to the entrance (or just die and run back in) from here you jump down just behind the group at the door to the viewing room beneathe you. if you take a while to study the way they move you can move inside without getting aggro. otherwise ss ftw!\
the mobs in ras' room are cake, and the lab is just to your right. congrats you're done!",
