    "57814044530404452007/02/22 09:27:18azerothrulerYou can see an NPC named Taelon in Old Hillsbrad Foothills instance, in one of the houses of Southshore. He wields this toy hammer.",
    "57816354831310212007/04/07 23:59:31wpd184First off, you have to be 52 in order to get this quest, second, you need to be 50 to get Dragons Breath, so this is not possible if you are a 47 Fire Mage.",
    "57811917460191742007/01/03 06:08:53NinesThere is no need to kill him last.\
\
Just did it on my 59 rogue killed him first, looted him and received Taelen's Hammer from him - the 3 cronies were still alive.\
\
But this only worked if i did not CC one of them first.  If i sapped one of them at all then i couldn't loot the hammer no matter in what order they died.\
\
Now this may apply to other forms of CC but it certainly applies to the sapping of the target.  I just spent a good hour testing this out, and at least in my case this is what occured.\
\
I just used Mechanical Yeti and he took the damage long enough for me to tear Mercutio down loot the hammer and vanish.",
    "5781185811018582006/10/14 06:04:43rubadubOK, this is extremely difficult to solo as a rogue, but I just did it as a 59 rogue.  I am combat spec with a 16.57% chance to crit (not sure if that will make sense once BC comes along, but anyway...) it took me a few tries to figure out how to do it... first thing is make sure you have major healing potion or two.\
\
First click the mound of dirt next to the gravestone.  The mobs walk in instead of spawning right away so immediately stealth.  Next, if you wait for them to get to the grave they start to mill about, which makes it a bit hard to position yourself, so distract them before they get to the grave. Cheap shot Mercutio and immediately use evasion.  This should keep you alive for most of the fight.  once evasion wears off, blind one of the graverobbers to try and lessen the DPS intake.  Also watch out for your health as you'll need that health pot eventually...  I was close to dying so once mercutio fell I Vanished.  His body didn't disappear or anything, so I waited a few seconds for a bit of health to come back.  Once I had some health I looted the corpse real quick and sprinted away.\
\
Hope this helps someone...",
    "5781128035212992007/07/28 00:12:51dotsBody despawns if you die without killing all the mobs. If you plan to suicide it, loot the body before it hits the ground.\
\
57 shaman pull with 2x lightning bolt, flameshock, stormstrike.\
Then stoneclaw totem, lightning shield, es, ss, stoneskin totem, es, loot, die, ankh",
    "578146907110469072007/03/06 03:57:07aerohCoords: 28:86",
    "5781201672102016722007/12/15 09:53:39UlteraIt *is* possible as a feral druid. (was 57 at the time)\
\
My sequence (you should only attack Mercutio): Open grave. Back up so you don't aggro them right away. Cast Regrowth, followed by Rejuvenation. Switch to bear form. Faerie Fire, Demoralizing Roar then swich it up between Mangle and Maul. You can also use Frenzied Regeneration when it's warranted. When you're around 40-50%, cast Barkskin. Heal yourself with Healing Touch, then follow it up with Regrowth and Rejuvenation. (Use a healing potion if you need to, they *might* kill you before you get the first heal off) Switch back to Bear Form. Mangle/Maul until Mercutio's dead. Shift-click his body so you auto-loot, go into Travel Form, run away with his kid's little toy warhammer.",
    "5781196496101964962007/12/05 14:30:16SkytheSCThis was not easy to solo as a resto Shaman at 55, but here is how I did it.\
\
Started by clearing out all the trolls around the grave, and those along the fence and in the trees behind it. Earth shield up and dropped an earthbind totem behind the fence. Opened the grave and let the guys spawn, then jumped over the fence and stood behind the totem.\
Let them stop at the grave then pulled Mercutio with a lightning bolt, then used natures swiftness to cast another one isntantly. Then I ran around dropping earthbinds whenever the cooldown was up and using frost shock to slow him down (since it is off DRs again). Took about 4 tries sometimes I would get a troll or get gouged and beaten down. If you are a resto Shaman at level 55 I would recommend just getting some help to avoid the repair bill.\
\
-Used 1 major healing potion.\
\
Hope this helps anyone, was a very annoying quest.",
