    "4743118973201189732007/07/11 08:58:20MareynWhen MC'ing Emberstrife, you will actually have *two* abilities that involve the breathing of fire.  One of them, the second from the left, has an icon with a flame on it and is called \"Breath of Flame\", \"Flame Breath\", or something similar.  This is NOT the one you want to use, as it does not convert an Unforged Seal of Ascension into a forged one.\
\
The other fire breathing ability, which is the first from the left, is actually called \"Flame of the Black Dragonflight\" and is the one you want to use.  Its icon is a yellow inscription of some sort that looks nothing like a flame.\
\
The reason I mention this is because when I did the quest, either something in my UI obscured the FotBD icon or I didn't see it in all the clutter, so the only relevant ability I saw was Emberstrife's standard flame breath attack.  Needless to say, I was frustrated when I used up three of my Orb of Draconic Energy's charges and the ability didn't forge the seal.  After researching more online and disabling all my addons to ensure that the FotBD icon would be visible, I tried again and it worked.\
\
It should also be noted that the Orb of Draconic Energy and the Unforged Seal of Ascension both have 5 charges each.  It is unconfirmed as to whether you need to redo the entire quest line--i.e., re-gathering the 3 rare-drop gems--if you use up all 5 charges; on Allakhazam's entry for this quest, a user named KEmperor reported in January 2006 that the quest could be abandoned and picked up again without having to re-collect the gems, but another individual on the same thread reported one year later that it wasn't possible, and that they had to repeatedly ask a GM to restore their gems before the request was granted.\
\
I had originally assumed that this quest was frustrating simply because collecting the rare-drop gems was difficult.  I was not aware that there was actually a very confusing and unforgiving quest that followed it; to top it off, as someone mentioned earlier in this thread, the quest has been bugged for at least 5 months such that even after you have the Forged Seal of Ascension, you need to re-obtain an Unadorned Seal of Ascension to complete the quest.  As such, this is easily the most poorly-designed quest chain I have ever undertaken, and I am very disappointed with Blizzard.",
