    "82197146101971462007/12/06 21:56:58AwlbisteConfirmed 4500xp at level 45. I was killing yellow 47 and orange 48 stingers around the edges. Drop rate seemed around 30% for me. Also added stay away from the swarmers they come with about 10 adds.",
    "82144729101447292007/08/27 07:58:26AevitasThe Noxious Lair is located around 37,39. The quest items drop from all of the insects around the Noxious lair, and have a drop rate of around 20%. This quest is even doable around level 46-47, if you know what to do.\
\
You'll find a variety of mobs around there, including:\
- Centipaar Swarmer\
- Centipaar Wasp\
- Centipaar Sandreaver\
- Centipaar Worker\
- Centipaar Stinger\
\
The Sandreaver and the Wasp are just easy fights, without any adds.\
However, the Swarmer calls in ads, which also damage you, and if you're a caster will prevent you from casting. If you can, lay down an AOE every 5 or 10 seconds to wipe all these little mobs. They have around 5 HP, and should be oneshotted with one AOE hit. I'm a hunter myself, and I used Volley to get rid of all the insects in one shot. Also Multi Shot works. For Paladins, try to use Consecration, Mages use Arcane Explosion. Any class that can't do AOE shouldn't try to engage these mobs around level 45-47, but wait untill level 49-50 or so. \
\
However, they can do the other mobs found around the area.\
Done this quest with a warlock, hunter, paladin, mage and a rogue myself now, and I've only had trouble with the rogue around level 46, for the other classes it was easy.",
