  ["Triage45"] = {
    "66244535npcDoctor Gustaf VanHowzen12939npcDoctor Gustaf VanHowzen129393900",
    "66243641040364102007/02/15 11:20:30CrandorfFirst off, this is the Alliance side triage (see the horde one for hints about that one)\
\
Prepare to get the quest, and its bandages.\
Clear up a slot in your backpack so you know where the bandages will appear.\
Also pull your #1 button (your \"attack\") to free up that quick key for the bandages you will get.\
Stand as close to the center of the room as you can and still get the quest.\
\
Open your backpack, accept the quest, grab the quest bandages and drop them in your #1 quick key.\
Spin around and look for the worst off person in the following order:\
          critically injured \
          badly injured \
          whoever has been on bed the longest\
\
Click on most critical\
     If too far away you should be able to walk 1 or 2 steps to get to them.\
Then click on quick key to start the bandaging.\
\
While you bandage, turn around and look for the next target.\
     Use the right-mouse to turn so you don’t break the bandaging.\
Mouse over the others and select the next victim.\
     Left click to target them (it wont break the current bandaging)\
\
As soon as the last bandaging is done, quick key the next one to start and repeat.\
\
If you somehow fail this quest\
     Abandon the quest\
     Toss out the bandages given before.\
     And try it again.",
    "66241055302001055302007/06/16 16:00:01AshleyBring 75 Mageweave Cloth and 70 Runecloth with you.  You can train all of the bandages after completing the quest, and eliminate having to return to him in the future.\
\
1) After you finish quest, the doctor will train you automatically. Make Mageweave bandages. Talk to doctor again at 240.\
2) 241-260 make Heavy Mageweave bandages.\
3) 261-290 make Runecloth bandages.\
4) 291-300 make Heavy Runecloth bandages.\
\
I have used this for five characters.  Works like a charm.",
    "6624256227025622006/11/02 14:15:03lawlitronAllows training of Artisan First Aid (Up to 300).\
\
When doing the quest, 3 types of patients spawn: Injured, Badly Injured and Critically Injured. You must save 15 patients before 6 perish.\
\
Bandage the Critically Injured victims first, as they live the shortest. Once all Critically Injured victims are healed, proceed to heal Badly Injured victims. Again, once all have been healed, proceed to heal Injured victims.",
    "66244869620486962007/03/09 12:03:51lyzzardThere's no need to abandon the quest if you fail. A message will pop up if you fail and the exclamation mark appears over the doc's head again. Just speak to him to repeat the quest, no limit to the number of times you can attempt it.\
\
Instead on clicking on the individual patients, use the V or Ctrl-V (Mac) key and click on the name plates instead. There will usually be 5 or 6 name plates present so click on the order of severity of injuries to heal. Really easy.",
    "662417719321486962007/10/31 07:59:51IcelusAs of 2.2.3 this no longer works. I just did the quest on an alt and the first thing I did was hit CTRL+V but to my surprise, no health bars appeared.",
    "6624263827125622006/11/03 10:41:47TheOnyxA tip: Once you have started using the Triage Bandage on one of the soldiers, you can select another one as your target. You'll mend the one you originally had targeted and be set up to mend the next one at the press of a button once you've patched up the first one.\
\
That, combined with mending the soldiers in the correct triage order (see above), made this quest a lot easier on me than when I first tried to do it.",
    "6624599418059942006/12/05 10:01:45OrmrissCouple of more tips:\
\
-Stand in the middle of the patients.  You should be able to reach them all, especially doing this on Horde side.\
\
-If you still can't finish this, team up with someone else who needs the quest and do it at the same time.  A two person team still only has to save 15 patients total, which is much easier.",
    "662415247621713502007/09/13 12:27:52titaniumpenAgreed! I tried doing it the critically, badly, and injured order first and failed. Did it from the left going around (even missed one or two) and completed it.",
    "6624204673111488862007/12/20 19:52:31djet13Wrong. I didn't get the prequest and I sat next to the doctor and leveled up to 225 and when i hit it, BAM the yellow ! popped up. It may have not have been the same before 2.3 though.",
    "6624207963111488862007/12/27 02:52:52bubbaThat prequest has never been necessary. As the poster above said, just hit 225 and it will become available.",
    "662471350170713502007/04/23 01:54:40EliseMy tip is:\
