\
Placed the bandage on my hotbar, easy does it!",
    "662416993811713502007/10/16 17:17:00JerodastJust wanted to add my agreement to Elise's suggestion...the respawn takes long enough that going in a circle means that nobody is lying on a bed long enough to die before you get to them as long as you go in a consistent order. It's also easy to target the next guy. I do recommend you skip the critically injured unless they spawn RIGHT in the next spot, since they will die before you finish the bandage probably. However, there aren't many of them, so this wont fail you. Anyway, followed this technique after failing once, and  got it the first time.",
    "66247389271713502007/04/27 13:17:55AdiAptaElise's tip to start from the left [or right] and go around WORKED!  I did the quest alone & tried all other ways; critically injured, badly injured, then injured.  The order doesn't matter.   Going in a circle around the room is the BEST way to do this quest!  I tried it once and I completed the quest.",
