    "3372203109302031092007/12/17 22:39:15TudeAll good advice here so far, but its all mixed up into bits and confusing pieces, hopefully this clarifies it all into one post.\
\
Exit the cave. Should be easier to head east uphill to leave.\
\
Head back towards Thorium Point, continue past it to about 24, 29. It loooks a bit like a cobblestone path. Follow the torches a bit to your right until you see the lava pool. Clear the mobs. Stand on the Twighlight Artifact in the middle of the lava pool and click it. Lava gives a lot of damage, so be sure to do this.\
\
Return to the cave where you got this quest. I found it easiest to drop down from about 49,44 which lines you up with the cave that easiest to go back to. \
\
The Altar Of Suntara is next to where you got the quest. Click on it. 5,800 XP as of patch 2.3.\
\
Quest continues with Rise, Obsidian, which requires you to stand there for a minute, they spawn right in front of you and that quest is returned to Ironforge for 8,650 XP.",
