    "4135142255401422552007/08/22 12:46:20shoobiehater345I found a rare spawn in this cave as well named Qirot, a white stinger (lvl 47, non elite). he was flying around the pod, so i blew him up. not hard, really. (45 frost mage)",
    "4135347742118472006/11/11 18:02:10ecornicAlso, make sure you're going into the Westernmost hive, instead of the one in the East which holds nothing!",
    "41359234780923472007/05/28 09:28:08CyaniaAlso there's a flying bug patrolling and it comes in the room too so watch out.",
    "4135183145201831452007/11/12 23:10:30KhamoraTo help with picking the right cave, once you're at the bottom of the spiral, facing the opposite wall, you will have a cave on your right, and two caves (one on top of another) on your left.  Take the left BOTTOM cave of course staying to your right as Nifty said.  Don't go too fast, there are a couple mobs along the tunnel as you go.  Don't run into the cave as soon as you see the pod, there is a bug on either side of the entrance.  Move to one side and take that bug first, then go for the others one at a time.  Done without heals on a 48 feral druid, I only killed the mobs on the way and the two on either side of the pod, I didn't have to go after the third.  The mobs do dodge and parry a lot so it's best if you are at least level 46, in case the patrolling bug aggros.  Don't worry about Raschal, once he is out of the pod he *stealths* on his own, stay next to him until you get the *complete* message on your screen.  Then you can either stealth/prowl out or fight more insects if they've respawned.",
    "4135131948101319482007/08/04 00:00:12ArtesynCoordinates for the Zukk'ash Pod are 71/63.",
