    "7603608012060802006/12/05 11:20:15MahmothSoloable at 60 or thereabouts.  The key to killing him is that he's Fearable, so you can mostly just wait 'till he's risen, Fear him, DoT him up, then send your pet after him.  He spawns in a nice, isolated bit of Felwood, so you almost certainly won't have any problems with adds from the craters.  Make sure you keep an eye on him in case Fear breaks early.  Keep a Health and SoulStone up, just in case, and if all else fails, banish'n'bandage.",
    "76036290620629062007/04/06 11:18:40WebbRemains at 45,3-35.3.",
    "7603148374201483742007/09/02 23:11:24VonaSolo'd as lv.51 Affliction Warlock with Imp (Had to re-spec. from my PvP favourite Dest.) Took around 7/8 attempts due to resists. Used 4 bandages and 2 healthstones in the end, Defiler's Talisman also came in handy when fear resisted.\
\
Start with Fear then CoA, then Corruption. Keep fearing at around 50% of duration of current fear just to be sure, plus Dark Pact when needed. I had to spam the instant casts due to resists. If it all goes wrong keep Death Coil at the ready and then spam fear right after that > once you get your distance again check your DoTs and reapply if needed - then check mana, then check distance - just repeat and with a little luck you should be fine.\
\
He had me down to less than 10% health each time I used a bandage. Make sure you bandage immediately after the fear lands, or potion + HS if you panic. :) Don't use mana potions, save potion cooldown for the health potion + HS combo.\
\
Keep your range also (I had my spells down the right actionbar in order to keep track of the red dots) Luckily at 50% he got jammed slightly behind a tree after running up the side wall so distance was easy to track. As long as you keep your distance you won't get beat down, concentrate about landing DoTs after you feel safe enough to fit them in.",
    "76031433090143302006/12/12 16:42:44grovestandThis quest is easily soloable at 50-53. Be careful, and be patient on this kill:\
\
There are two key spells you will need on this one: Curse of Agony and Fear. I suggest using your imp for the stamina buff, for you might need extra mana via lifetap later if you wish to use corruption as well.\
\
Start the fight, do NOT attack with your imp. Cast fear first, followed by curse of agony, and corruption if you wish. Kroshius is immune to fire spells, so no immolate. Apply Curse of agony and fear as necessary, and when he is at about 10 percent, feel free to nuke him at will. \
This fight can take up to 10 minutes, so be sure to remain patient. \
When kroshius dies, return to Impsy, and be prepared for a glorius suprise that will be a thing to remember =D",
    "7603170507101705072007/10/17 14:26:43redandgrayIf you are lucky, you can enslave [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=7137]Immolatus[/url], a 56 elite rare spawn that wanders the area. He will take down Kroshius fairly quickly, then you can sic him on an elemental while you loot Kroshius's corpse and high-tail it out of there. Just remember that you have to do at least one point of damage to Kroshius yourself in order to get quest completion.",
    "7603200330102003302007/12/12 17:55:16GzillaSoloed very easily at 51. I'm demo/affliction specced, but I don't think felguard is neccessary.  He is a level 55 non elite, and was not immune to fire, or shadow.  Just feared him and sent my felguard onto him immediately as he hostiled.  Dot stacked, and then drained to death. No adds, no difficulty.  Easiest part of the quest, in my honest opinion.",
