( If you don't know Kralnor, first shame on you, then read up http://wowwiki.com/Kralnor )",
    "8422162260116212006/10/08 14:43:39SkosirisAccording to the Quick Facts box above, both Horde and Alliance players can do this quest.",
    "8422201915102019152007/12/15 17:29:47I0wrld3rWhy would you need the shard anyway? At this level, I didn't use my Voidwalker. It was my succubus all the time. As for the chest, I prefer sets, so that I look right, rather than wearing a bit of Shadoweave (purple) and then some green robe. So in the end, I'll choose the staff. It may be replaceable, but I don't usually spend money.",
    "84224956131403732007/03/11 14:25:23AraceliaI took the Abyss shard and have confirmed that you do get a soul shard like normal, so it can give you a free soul shard every half hour. You can also simply tell your voidwalker to \"Stay\" and then when you walk out of range and it should give you a soul shard back too.",
    "8422207968112019152007/12/27 03:15:15weazle[quote]Why would you need the shard anyway? At this level, I didn't use my Voidwalker. It was my succubus all the time.[/quote]\
and \
[quote]It may be the best and the most durable, but what's the problem with missing a Soul Shard and an amount of mana that'll be back in no-time (life tap and Drain life in the next fight?). And when you don't use the Voidwalker, this thing is just useless.[/quote]\
A)\
The succubus is your favorite minion. You are out of Soul Shards and your succubus isn't summoned. Not one mob that generates XP is in sight. You want to summon the succubus. What will you do?\
1. Use the Abysss Shard to summon the Voidwalker.\
2. Tell the VW to Stay.\
3. Run away from the VW until it is out of sight: You will get a Soul Shard.\
4. Summon the succubus.\
\
B)\
You are a Demonology spec Warlock. You are in a tough battle, solo. Both your HP and mana are low, and you are getting aggro. Your minion's HP is low too. What will you do?\
1. Cast Fel Domination and use the Abysss Shard to summon the Voidwalker. \
2. Choose to sacrifice the VW and run away (to fight another day) and/or choose to let VW attempt to tank (giving you time to use pots and/or bandages).\
\
I am sure there are other senarios :).\
\
[quote]Since this is a levelling quest, take the item that benefits you most at the time. That simple.[/quote]\
Each quest reward has advantages: Who am I to say that choosing the staff or the robe is \"wrong\"? But, I see at least a few people, already with level 70 Warlocks, who are posting here (and other sties) and are now saying they are going for the Abyssal Shard. True, these are rewards for a levelling quest, but the Abyssal Shard lasts forever (including times when you willl no longer be levelling ).",
