  ["Mea Culpa, Lord Valthalak60"] = {
    "899560npcBodley16033npcSpirit of Lord Valthalak160739950189851898618987289892899028991389944899558996",
    "89951475680147562006/12/13 09:17:56kreghxTalk about a difficult fight! This guy is a total pita! \
\
Prior to downing Valthalak we killed Ossirian and Nef on the same night. Of the 3 fights everyone in my group agreed that Valthalak was the most difficult. I am not sure if Blizzard scales the difficulty depending on your gear but considering how much trouble we had with him this is definitely possible. \
\
Our group consisted of the following \
\
1 Warrior \
2 Paladins \
1 Priest (me) \
1 Warlock \
3 Rogues \
1 Mage \
1 Hunter \
\
Almost all players had some tier 2 and a good amount of tier 1. I personally had 3 tier 2 and 3 tier 1 with Benediction. \
\
Our strategy for our successful attempt went like this: \
\
Our tank pulled Valthalak to the wall where you stage to kill the Beast. He was accompanied by 1 rogue to kill adds that appear close to Valthalak. All others stood back and DPSed with a primary focus on the adds. The lock and occasionally the hunter focused on burning his mana. This is very important as when he has mana he seems to heal himself. Our mage also hit him with improved counter spell whenever possible. \
\
After 40% stage 1 ends and it is an easy fight as it is just a matter of DPSing him down and keeping the main tank up. \
\
Vent was very helpful as we could call out when we were being stunned so that no one died due to being stunned for the full 8 seconds. \
\
Even with this strat it was not easy and did not go perfectly. I died just as stage 1 ended as he hit me with a shadow bolt that did 4700 damage. Our tank died when Valthalak had about 10K health remaining as our palies were out of mana. Thankfully the remaining members were able to do some awesome DPS and finished him quickly. \
\
Things to remember \
\
1  Burn his mana \
2  Kill the adds as fast as possible",
