    "7641177141017712006/10/11 14:20:27CreeestopherPaladin Epic Mount Questline:\
\
Step 1:  The Paladin trainer in the Cathedral in SW gives you 2 quest lines to complete:\
--\
Step 2A: Emphasis on Sacrifice  (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7637) (Priest in IF)\
Just need to fork over 150 gold.  (And you thought Paladins got free mounts)\
\
Step 3A: To Show Due Judgment  (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7639)\
Take the Censer back to Grayson.\
\
Step 4A: Exorcising Terrordale  (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7640)\
Head to Terrordale in the NW part of the Eastern Plaguelands.  Stand in the green circles and push use your Censer.  Kill 25 of these dudes and head back to Grayson.\
--\
Step 2B:  The Work of Grimand Elmore (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7641)\
Head to the Dwarven District in SW and talk to him.\
\
Step 3B:  A Collection of Goods (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7642)\
You need to pick up a lot of mats for this step, and another 150 gold.\
\
- 5 Stratholme Holy Water (From the crates in Stratholme)\
- 10 Arthas Tears (Pick em if youre an Herbalist, otherwise get them from the AH)\
- 40 Runecloth (drops, AH)\
- 6 Arcanite Bar (AH)\
\
Once you round these up, head back to Grimand and shell out your 150 gold.  Then head back to Grayson to get the next step.\
\
Step 4B:   Manna-Enriched Horse Feed (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7645)\
You need to be friendly with the Argent Dawn.  Buy 20 manna biscuits from them and head to the horse trainer in Southshore.  Give the horse trainer the biscuits and 50 gold and youre good to go.  Once again, head back to Grayson.\
--\
Step 5:  Ancient Equine Spirit (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7643) \
Head to Dire Maul to find an ancient spirit of a horse.  In Dire Maul west there is a treant, Tendris Warpwood, that you need to kill.  Once you kill him, the spirit of the horse will come out and you can talk to it.\
\
Step 6:  Blessed Arcanite Barding (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7644)\
Talk to the horse, it will bless your barding.  Once youve done this, head back to Grayson.  Before you do so, pick up an Azerothian Diamond and a Pristine Black Diamond (both from AH)\
\
Step 7:   The Divination Scryer (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7646)\
Give the diamonds to Grayson and hell give you the scryer.  Make sure you have the blessed barding with you when you do this.  Hell give you a satchel that has the scryer and the barding in it.\
\
Step 8:   Judgment and Redemption (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=7647)\
Take the satchel and a group to Scholomance and work you way to Rattlegores room. \
\
A quick note about groups.  A priest will be very necessary so that you can shackle.  The more pallies you have, the better.  Id recommend 3 so that you can alternate judgments.  A warlock would be nice for soulstone and overall dps, but if youre not worried about dying, you could throw in a mage or a rogue.  But for the final battle, paladins are more important than others.\
\
Clear Rattlegores room and have everyone stand in the corner to the right of the door.  One of the pallies needs to run to the opposite corner (as close as they can get) and place the scryer on the floor.  Once the scryer is down, the event begins.  It is important to stay as far in the corner as you can so that you can rest at points in the event.\
\
The key to the event is using judgments.  Each wave needs a different judgment.  Judging the correct spell on each wave provides you with an AoE shock on the ghosts.  The more paladins you have, the more often you can have the mobs stunned and the better off youll be.  Set up a judging order and make sure everyone knows the order.  Have the 1st pally judge the correct spell and then count to 5 and have the next pally judge.\
\
The order is Wisdom, Justice, Righteousness, and finally Light.  When you get down to the last ghost in the last wave, have the priest shackle it and have everyone mana up because once the last ghost is down, the charger boss shows up.  \
\
Kill him and youve got a shiny new epic mount!",
