    "763123407220234072007/01/24 00:17:09HaydiesIf anyone is struggling with the quest chain, sections or general information, there is a guide located at The Warlocks Den ( http://wowmb.net/index.php?page=Dreadsteed ) that might prove helpful.",
    "763148148048142006/11/27 11:34:10rlyehDoing this quest with a second warlock is very nice even if you don't need their Bell, Wheel, and Candle.\
\
DM West is rather easy for Warlocks due to their banish spell.  Having 2 'locks makes taking down the pylons very easy.\
\
Having 2 'locks around for enslave demon during the Xorothian Dreadsteed event is sometimes the edge you need to succeed.  Since the elite demons spawn at a certain rate during the event, it is possible to fall behind and then it becomes very diffictult to finish.   With a second 'lock handy it's no trouble to have 2 elite demons controlled and fighting one (or two if you're really behind in dps) elite demon(s). \
\
Plus two 'locks handing out healthstones and using soulstones makes for a fast rebound from a bad situation or wipe.\
\
Good luck.",
    "7631121146101211462007/07/15 16:46:58AvaloniaIf you don't have a lot of friends or a decent guild on your server that are willing to help just save yourself some time and frustration and buy your epic mount training and either pvp for the epic mount or just buy it. What you save in frustration is much more than 100-200g difference you save by doing the quest. I really wish Blizzard would update these so that they become Ramparts/Blood Furnace quests so that people will actually run them.",
    "76317038011696162007/04/21 06:23:39blackhornI wouldn't necessarily mod this down.  He has a point.  I'm a 70 lock looking to do the final part of DM and its taken a long time to get the Scholo group (precursor to DM part) and now to get the DM group.  People simply do not do these instances anymore.\
\
What you can do is offer ot take people in their high 50s through, but this means that both instances will still end up being a challenge as they are geared for people 59-60.  All of which are in outlands getting better xp and gear than you can offer.\
\
If you are looking to do this chain simply to get a fast mount, you really are better off getting an epic mount one of the myriad other ways until Blizzard (if ever) sees fit to update this quest.",
    "76314280331270462007/02/26 14:03:15webtekkieYes, and as others have pointed out, the first part of the ritual DOES NOT require you to kill all the mobs, just to survive long enough during the first phase of the ritual. Banishing and AOE makes this much easier. This is why having multiple locks is a godsend.\
\
We ran this with 3 locks, tank, and priest. 2 locks were on banish and AOE patrol, and the last one did nothing but refresh artifacts.\
\
Also, you can have as many locks as you want complete the last phase of the quest by inviting them in the group to talk to the spirit. They just have to be on the last part of the chain. This was true as of a month or so after BC was released.",
    "763110097941976532007/06/08 20:22:44DeragalloIf you're unable to find people to go. You might try joinging a guild (assuming you aren't already in one.) and seeing if your guildmates could help out. Otherwise, try advertising on the realm forum that you're looking for some help with the quest.",
    "763110540111696162007/06/16 10:59:06singularityThe scholo step is pretty easy for a 70 lock to solo.  I did it and only died once.",
    "76317038111661312007/04/21 06:33:25blackhornI have done DM West with a 70 hunter and 57 priest all the way to Immolthar with no trouble, but could not complete immolthar because his aggro dump (drop kicking you into the air) means he will kill your healbot.  I added a 56 pally into the mix and completed without difficulty.\
\
I used this same hunter at 70 to help a 66 warlock get her mount, we had a full group composed of a 56 druid, 62 priest and 57 paladin.  While we completed the summoning ritual first time, it was still a bit hair raising because we lacked good aoe and the warlock had to spend her time refreshing the ritual components.\
\
I think your minimum group to make it a painless experience would be the 70 lock, any 57+ healer, and a 65+ warrior or mage.  I think you could complete with that setup.",
    "76318594611728552007/05/19 22:36:25darukaruYeah, you don't actually receive these as in-bag items. You can buy the black lodestone at the last stage of the quest, and if you buy the imp jar that supposedly has your bell/wheel/candle in it.",
