    "481002511120212007/06/07 14:42:32mommyclzOk, the location wasnt quite as hard to find as I though after reading your post. Here's my coord-less description.\
\
First of all, check out this map of the fountain location: http://www.wowhead.com/?object=759\
\
Now, head north from booty bay. You come to a wall of rock on your left, starting about the same level as the big island off the coast. As soon as you see the wall end, turn left. There will probably be a gorrilla or two there. \
\
Basically, you will walk uphill in a spiral. Hug the path to your left. You follow the wall until you come to a path heading left. Follow it accross the bridges and take the first path heading to the left, uphill. This is where the nagas show up. Watch the wall to your left, and you will see an arched entrance. Kill nagas and go straight across the rope bridge. \
\
Was very easy as 42 hunter, could be challanging at a lower level. Fun to see new and scenic spot, tho!",
