Done as 43 warlock, sacrificed when I had about 50% of health, then used HS, walked over the altar and jumped down from the left side ^^",
    "298917967411591262007/11/05 16:07:53gobuzzworked just as well with a 44 rogue",
    "298919353111628972007/11/29 18:46:42astoryundoneI couldn't get the 'stealth behind the altar' thing to trigger as a 44 druid. So I just chugged a Free Action Potion and RAN up the steps. The trolls hitting me didn't stun me, and I survived just long enough for the quest to complete. Had I actually made it over the edge, I would have survived. But the quest finished anyway, so I didn't care.",
    "2989225932022592006/10/26 01:02:41DoranosTo complete this quest you just have to run up to the altar.  The hard part is there are level 50 elite trolls on that altar.  Use whatever speed increase, or evasion tatic you have and rush up to the altar and hop down and run off.  If you can't stealth you will probably die trying to run away afterward but at least you will have the quest completed.",
    "29896289710628972007/04/06 07:09:07NimfoJust FYI if you can stealth around to the left or right side of the altar and go behind it, it will complete your quest, and it can be done with no aggro (in stealth) no cogs to use, just walk to it.\
\
There's a chest behind the alter if you can get to it, but I'm not going to try that chest until higher level!\
\
lvl 46 druid",
    "2989339586122592007/02/11 07:04:12InfernoManIf you are lucky enough to be an Alchemist, or have a friend who is one, then this becomes REALLY easy.  Make (or have your friend make you) a lesser invisibility potion, kill the 2 or three trolls that are on the steps, take the potion right about the top of the steps, you can run up to the middle of the altar till it says quest completed, turn around and head back down the stairs before the potion wears off.",
    "29896314820631482007/04/07 01:14:45xxbmxbrianxxThis quest was actually pretty simple.. I completed it as a 44 rogue. Just stay to the side and then you can go behind everything and then to the middle until it says you've comepleted your quest and then you can jump down from either side. it's a pretty simple quest for rogues.. not sure about anything else..",
    "29898200611775132007/05/12 18:40:57waylorI was also a 46 warrior, i just used bloodrage, stood at the top of the steps until it was over, charged a guy, and then used intimidating shout and feared most of them, then i jumped off the side with over half my life left, and the people on the ground only hit me a little, just try to avoid them.",
    "29896578720657872007/04/11 22:48:57BargleI managed to easily complete it as a 44 shaman by just running up through the middle.  If you go straight over the top after the stairway, you can jump over the back of the altar and go under the ledge and the mobs will reset.",
    "2989174076201740762007/10/24 03:54:44vexis58If you happen to be a gnomish engineer, the Gnomish Cloaking Device makes this quest easy to solo. Just use it near the top of the stairs, run in until the quest is complete, then run back to the stairs. Nothing on the top will aggro on you while you're invisible.",
    "2989197551101975512007/12/07 16:41:13WyrickThere is an even better way to do this. Clean the first few on the stair (they are around level 45) then take your mount, run up, run straight through the elites and jump down behind them. And no one will attack you anymore. If you didn't run straight through them, you can rest here and restore health to try it a second time. That way it worked for me in the third try, because I wasn't sure where I need to go (You need to go to the middle of the altar).\
\
Hope that helps.",
    "2989196284101962842007/12/05 06:04:57SaulusI have a trick: use invisibility potion. That's the easiest way to do this for lo-lvl non-stealth classes :).",
    "2989157817701578172007/09/24 19:52:15ElcmarI haven't seen anyone mention this, so I will.  While you can indeed just run up to the top of the temple to complete this quest, if you later want to summon [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=7273]Gahz'rilla[/url] in ZF to complete that quest, you need to actually kill the level 50 elite [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=7996]Qiaga the Keeper[/url].  She drops the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=9241]Sacred Mallet[/url], which can be transformed into the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=9240]Mallet of Zul'Farrak[/url], which is used at the gong inside ZF to summon Gahz'rilla.\
\
I highly recommend bringing a high level with you, just so you can get the mallet.  It's frustrating to be in the middle of ZF and realize no one in your group can summon Gahz'rilla.",
    "29895912610591262007/03/29 11:21:06cricktonthis quest was really easy with my lvl 47 rogue. just stealth up there, and use distract on the troll on either side of the alter, walk up on the later, and walk away.",
    "29891384541122592007/08/15 17:00:23ZerhynnOr, if you're a Paladin, just bubble at the top of the stairs, and you can get to the Altar and out of the entire place before bubble wears off.  If it does wear off, Blessing of Freedom yourself.",
    "29897532418122592007/04/30 06:48:34DimstormIt's right at 49,68.\
\
Completed as 46 Warlock. Simple...charge in on your mount, and when it kicks you off almost half way up the steps, sacrafice your VW and go straight over the top. Have a Healthstone handy in case you get stunned, but if you jump off the back of the altar over the ledge, the mobs reset.",
    "2989188034401880342007/11/20 01:04:19dixierebel2020actually, since 2.3, the guys at the top of the altar are no longer elite, just a little higher level, one is a 50",
    "2989193097101930972007/11/29 02:49:05FyrfoxActually, there are two named 50's up there, very close together, plus another mob that might be a minion for one of them.  I  couldn't attempt Quiga without pulling the other 50.  \
\
The altar itself is very easy for a druid as long as you are high enough not to aggro the mobs while stealthed.  Just kitty stealth; you can walk right up and right back down again, no problem. Also, I got 6300 exp after the 2.3 patch.",
    "298917537311628972007/10/26 22:37:14bobahoyconfirmed; 44 rogue with MoD5",
