  ["Find OOX-17/TN!48"] = {
    "3514843itemOOX-17/TN Distress Beacon8623npcHoming Robot OOX-17/TN77844400Booty Bay25013512648",
    "351120094501200942007/07/13 15:28:22TheraxMap location of the (chicken) Homing Robot: http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=440:599640",
    "3516705710670572007/04/14 09:08:49PollyThis chicken is located at 60,64 in the mountains.\
I did this quest 4 times...\
at first i failed it when the 3 scorpions spawned around us...\
second time i failed because more mobs were wandering around this time...\
and third time i failed because of the 3 wastewanders that spawned around us after the scorpions...\
the fourth time i managed to complete it with hardly any mobs around.\
The trick to completing it for me was to kind of try and roughly remember the route that chicken takes, if you can do that then you can kill any mob around that area before taking on the quest - then you can easily escort it with no trouble. \
\
I did it with my lvl 50 Human Warrior, it was tricky even at that level...but another trick to doing it in one go especially as a warrior is to use intimidating shout for the 3 scorpions quickly kill one and if you have a good healing potion drink it and kill the other two...same applies to the 3 wastewander girls.\
\
I'm sure many people do this quest differently but i hope this helps :)",
    "351216330021632006/10/23 03:33:58PhogHawkThis leads to a rescue quest. The actual thing you need to find is the southermost \"dot\" on this map: http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=7784. Make sure you have another person if you're around the level that this quest is designed for, several adds are spawned at once in some cases and as a 46 mage I cannot take four scorpids with 2500 health each at once.",
    "35110780571569802007/06/20 08:39:34etherjammerYou're thinking of the second half of the quest.\
\
\"Find OOX-17/TN\", which is accepted when you activate the homing beacon and completed when you find the robot chicken in the southeast of Tanaris, gives 4400 XP and 250 rep.  \"Rescue OOX-17/TN!\", which is accepted at the robot chicken and completed when you get the chicken to Steamwheedle Port (but turned in in Booty Bay), gives 5400 XP and 350 rep.",
    "3518595620859562007/05/19 22:57:01SservisIf you want to solo these quests and need help, you can get Tooga to help if you haven't completed his quest (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1560).  Just be careful when the scorpians and bandits pop not to lose the chicken.  On the scorpians, the adds all went on Tooga and the chicken continued on its merry way.  I stayed to finish the adds and mounted to catch up, but I was a long way behind.",
    "3514674650467462007/03/05 19:38:25akmdwThe path that the robot takes is right through a group of 3 lvl 47 scorpids. Fortunately you can take them out beforehand. When you get near Steamwheedle port, a group of 3 wastewanders spawn, but they're all lvl 45.",
    "351113240101132402007/06/30 06:21:29caverDo you only get 1 shot at this? As when I died, I no longer had the quest item.",
    "3515698010569802007/03/25 13:16:38ChoperosActually the quest gives 5450 experience and 350 rep...Completed on the 25/3/07 as a lvl 49 warrior...",
    "35144395250443952007/03/01 06:23:03LizirThe location of the chicken is 60, 64.",
    "3516506321467462007/04/10 14:26:34bootsanatorDon't disregard the Wastewanders just because they're lower level. For me, one caster with a VW and two others spawned, and I killed the wrong two first. Yes, always kill casters first...escort quests are definitely not the time to forget that rule of thumb. The chicken died, then I died.\
Too bad, because those scorpids were Easy...yay for blade flurry, etc.",
    "35163937110639372007/04/08 15:18:20JohnJSalI'm going to post this message on all three of these \"Find\" quests, just in case someone doesn't see it on one of the other two.\
\
If you plan to do these quests in a group (which is very helpful, as any escort quest) everyone must first have completed the \"Find\" part of the quest, which means you have to find the chicken, choose \"Complete\" and then be *offered* the next part of the quest, which is the actual escort part. But do not accept this part until everyone has done the \"Find\" part, otherwise it won't be offered to them as escort quests normally are, because technically you are not on the same stage of the quest yet.\
\
So just complete the \"Find\" part, then when the next part is offered, decline it until everyone is ready to accept it.",
    "351203601102036012007/12/18 21:28:36BreakfirstHehe... I did this... Was not to hard... But then again, I cheated... Since I did it as a Hunter, and as allways that's ez-mode...\
\
Concentrate on 1, The multi-shoot, and feign death, if u run out of life.. (Well, ALMOST out of life), you should easily be able to finish them off then.. But remeber to look for mobs strolling around ur path.. ;)\
\
And a few bandages + Health pot never hurt any1... Good luck... Rest is as posted, reguarding position etc., and the reason the quest item is gone, is that the quest is completed, once you find the chicken.. The Escort-quest is the follow-up... Just abort, and go back to chicken start-position, if you die.. ;)",
    "3514845020484502007/03/08 22:04:34virginkillerIts not that hard just let the chicken to be in front and get the aggro so u cna have time to rest if the mobs are more than 1 kill them 1 at time i soloed it at 47lvl shaman",
    "351204572102045722007/12/20 16:30:18lilwolfyBe sure, that the chicken always enters combat when you fight. Just get close to the chicken, and let it aggro the mob.\
\
Otherwise, it might run forward, and you fail the quest.\
\
Not a bad idea to do this together with the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1560]Tooga's Quest[/url] There you have to escort a turtle, but the turtle is following you, and will help you in fight. In this case the quest is easily soloable by anyone.",
    "351117114111132402007/07/07 20:32:05nymonhNormally with rescue quests if you fail them, ie the person/chicken dies, you abandon them and return to the point you picked it up, and you can do it again.",
    "351207910102079102007/12/26 23:42:24PadimaiOk now spawn on this thing is really long and annoying.\
