    "348908409082006/09/23 04:29:22tykomykYou need to visit Witch Doctor Unbagwa (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=1449). He is in the cave just north of Booty Bay. You need to turn in 10 Gorilla Fangs to him and he will begin the summon. Waves of Enraged Silverback Gorillas appear and you need to protect him. The 1st wave is 3 gorillas, the second wave is 5 or 6. (I believe there are 4 waves, as of this posting, I have not yet completed it.)",
    "34812317150123172006/12/09 18:04:23dreampodQuite hard to solo this quest so find help if possible.\
\
First wave is 3 enraged Silverback Gorillas.\
Second wave is 3 enraged Silverback Gorillas, and a Gorilla named Konda for a total of 4 mobs.\
Third wave is 4 enraged Silverback Gorillas and Mokk himself.\
\
You only need to kill and loot Mokk to complete the quest, so make sure to focus your fire on him for the final wave since you can still complete the quest if you die after killing him.\
\
Between waves you have a couple seconds in which you can eat and drink.  If you have a pet or ally, you can send him out to attack to give you a bit of extra time as all the gorillas will turn to attack them.",
    "34898700100987002007/06/05 13:27:47ZesharSomething that I didn't notice mentioned:\
\
If you fail this quest by letting Unbagwa die before getting to Mokk, you will have to recollect 10 gorilla fangs.",
    "3487054820705482007/04/21 14:47:32SmorgesJust solo'd with my 44 fury warrior, i found out some neat tricks that might help out.\
\
on the first wave try to kill as many monkeys as you can before you get low on health once you do run away and deaggro all the monkeys that are left they will run back and start attacking the witch doctor bandage/eat&drink while he fights them for a while (he can take quite a bit) once you get your hp/mana back up go back and kill the rest of the monkeys\
\
on the second wave stand back a bit and let him pick up the aggro on some right away kill what you can then run a bit then come back and kill the rest and bandage/eat&drink up before the final wave\
\
on the last wave stand back and let him aggro as many as possible get the aggro on mokk and kill him fast loot his heart and run (or kill the rest if you can/want to)\
\
Hope this helps anyone trying to do this quest :)",
    "348194727801947272007/12/02 05:18:55Jubjub[b]This quest is very very easy. From booty bay run up to about 31,68 when you find Mistvale Gorilla's. Clear a path through them up to 35,61 (By then you should have obtained a Gorilla Fang) then talk to Witch Doctor Unbagwa. He won't have a yellow ? above his head for some reason, but is easy to find inside his cave. Once you speak to him, you will have a gap of about 10 seconds then a Enraged Silverback Gorilla (Level 43) will attack you. After him, another gap till Konda comes, another Level 43 Gorilla. Then you will have another gap till Mokk the Savage comes up (Level 44). Kill him and loot the Heart of Mokk. Return to Booty Bay and job done.\
Bearing in mind i was level 47 at the time, might be abit harder for you. I didn't even have to heal/drink/eat throughout the quest. \
Exterminated 47 Shaman - EU Zenedar. [/b]\
\
[Edit]: If Witch Doctor Unbagwa or you die before Mokk is dead, you will have to re-collect the Gorilla fang and start over.",
