    "902960objectFragrant Cauldron181073objectFragrant Cauldron181073",
    "9029101211401012112007/06/09 06:28:06zhekThis is the last quest for the Valentine's Day rewards.\
\
For horde, the quest line to get this begins with a [b]Deathguard Tor[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16003) located right outside the Undercity Zeppelin (Alternately, [b]Orok Deathbane[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16007) in Ogrimmar outside the bank, and [b]Temma of the Wells[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16008) in Thunderbluff.) . He will give you a card to give to [b]Elenia[/b] (Quest named: \"Dearest Elenia,\"). You give this to Elenia located around the UC bank (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16004).\
\
This finishes this part of the quest line, and a quest giver ([b]Fenstad[/b] http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16108) right next to her will have a quest (Quest named \"[b]Fenstad's Hunch[/b]\"). He sends you to [b]Apothecary Zinge[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=5204) located at the far back of the Apothecary District. She gives you the quest \"[b]Zinge's Assessment[/b]\", where you return to [b]Fenstad[/b]. Fenstad rewards you with a \"Box of Chocolates\" and a \"Handful of Rose Petals\".\
\
The next quest is \"[b]Tracing the Source[/b]\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8982), where he sends you to the Inn Keeper located on the top of the inner ring. [b]Inn Keeper Norman[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=6741) then sends you to [b]Mara Rennick[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16109) located at the UC Tailoring Shop (the quest is also named \"[b]Tracing the Source[/b]\" http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8983).\
\
Finally, she gives you \"[b]The Source Revealed[/b]\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8984), where you're asked to find [b]Apothecary Staffron Lerent[/b] (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16107). Lerent is located near Ravenhold Manor, which is in Hillsbrad. Once you're in the manor, head past the farm, (past the wall) up the hill, and down it, procede northeast until you see him.\
\
Turn in the quest, and MAKE SURE to click the cauldron nearby. The quest giver makes no indication of this, and this is how you get the reward. The cauldron gives a quest \"A Bubbling Cauldron\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=9029), and you get your choice of one of six vanity chest pieces, between red, blue, and purple \"Lovely Dress\" and the same colors for \"Dinner Suit\".\
\
The final part of this is identical for both factions, so other then the running around (I believe the quest has you running around Stormwind to much the same effect as Horde do in UC) you finish at the same spot. There typically seems to be people ganking due to the likelyhood of others showing up to get their reward, so watch out if you're on a PvP server, particularly since the cauldron isn't terribly obvious.\
\
The \"Lovely Black Dress\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=22279) isn't rewarded through this but is instead a rare gift given when turning in Love Tokens.",
    "9029128433111131592007/07/28 22:28:48AnaughtybearSadly, all the suits have to fit the character models as skin tight. I would like to see a patch that allows a tuxedo to look as though the wearer was going somewhere other than aerobics class.",
    "9029135864111131592007/08/11 09:40:21zhekThere are only a limited number of body types (two, robe, and no robe) for each race. Additionally boots and gloves have a limited number of shapes they can be in (something like 3-4 each). All leggings/chest pieces are skin tight. The reason is most likely they want to keep at a minimum the number of models a player has to load. For those slots, there's a very small number of choices. For more visable pieces (the shoulders and head pieces) they can be unique, although many head pieces share fairly common shapes across armor types.\
\
It reduces dramatically the amount of unique models to be loaded by streamlining the more basic pieces, and allowing the more visible ones to be the special pieces, basically.",
