    "6089213631822852007/05/28 02:02:44KineticI forgot to add that the Sea Dogs have a rather annoying backstab so never turn your back on them. This might be particulary tricky if you're running away from a bad pull and they're following right behind you.",
    "608162139111556922007/10/03 04:12:42rayzoriumDid solo on my 43 hunter, but it was extremely difficult and obnoxious, and I'd never do it again if given the choice. Getting range is nearly impossible inside the ship. To make things worse, my pet was lower level, so he got ridiculous glancing blows on some of the quest mobs (I saw quite a few single-digit hits). Top it off with my melee skill being equally ridiculously low. Perhaps a class that isn't so dependant on range would do better, or with self-healing. I'd really like to know what the hunter that posted before me did, because frost trap was largely useless for me, since I had nowhere to kite the mobs.\
\
As has been said before, the highest level you fight is a 48. In my case, he was linked with two level 45s. It should NOT be yellow to a level 43, which it was.",
    "608200614102006142007/12/13 08:07:14firejuggler6k xp for 2.3",
    "608209174112008062007/12/29 06:01:43VaratilThis is the same strategy I used. Here's a guide.\
Begin on the ramp onto the boat\
1. /tar cap or /tar fleet\
2. Send in pet\
3. When your target starts taking damage, call your pet back and back up.\
4. Make your pet stand still on the ramp while you stay on the ground\
5. FD\
6. Right as your pet dies pop out and Arcane shot your target\
Done right and you now have your quest mob with minimal clearing.\
Be sure to bring some extra food for your pet though.",
