    "608183915301839152007/11/14 02:34:40KaaosaAs of patch 2.3, this quest and the mobs associated with it have been scaled down to level 42.",
    "6083910080391002007/02/20 05:26:47asciidentAlthough the quest is marked level 45 (thus yellow to a level 43), be aware that Fleet Master Firallon is level 48 and surrounded by adds.",
    "608189290111839152007/11/22 05:02:54KintaConfirmed this one while on the quest. The only thing higher than level 42 were the two other spawns that were right next to the captain. Their names elude me at the moment, but one was an Orc, and one was a Tauren =] This quest is infinitely easier since the patch. The captains and the normal spawns were all 40-42.",
    "60819741811391002007/12/07 11:44:22RandithynsThey must have changed this. As a lvl 43 rogue, I stealthed by everyone, got in a corner in the fleet masters room, so not another mob could see me, I unstealthed and killed him easy.  He is now level 42 and I didn't aggro any other mobs.  Easy kill in the middle ship.",
    "608206286102062862007/12/23 23:40:44WasabiiSoloed him as a lvl 41 Prot Pali (2.6k health 4.8k armor). Sol/JoL were enough to keep me on par with his health, actually I ditched Sol for SoW halfway through, HS had drained my mana. Shielded and healed twice when he crit with a melee and then trample. Other wise he hit for about 90-110 crit for around 200 didn't catch how much trample did.\
Last edited by",
    "6089212611822852007/05/28 01:48:34KineticTrying to solo this quest below level 45 is a complete waste of time. I highly engourage you to bring a friend or two along due to the amount of adds you'll be dealing with. It's very hard to manage to pull 1-2 mobs within the boat where all the pirates patrol around and chain-pull even more mobs. If you're 45+ then this quest definitely is soloable - but depending on your class you might spend some time corpse running. And as stated above - make sure to have all the other pirate related quests and complete them as doing this one and what comes to the Riddle - I found it at Stillwater's ship.",
    "608189410101894102007/11/22 10:35:25sigmardinThis is all confirmed, its a simple quest now, the only small struggle would be the fact that the mobs are still close to each other and they respawn extremely quickly.\
   -- On a side note, there is a Solid Chest in the bottom floor of the ship with Fleet Master Firallon on it.  I didnt get any thing spectacular from it, but it did give me 2 greater healing pots, and some moonberry juice, some mageweave,and 2 greater mana pots.\
  ---Highest lvl i encountered was a 42 and i did this with my 43 enhance shaman with absolutely no problems",
