    "36281535501532006/09/13 04:49:03MerowlinIt is strongly suggested that you bring a 5 man party for this quest.\
\
There are serveral tactics to handle this quest, a good tactic would be to move everyone onto the lower part of the mountain. The tank should now pull him down there and turn his back towards the brick wall of the mountain (to avoid being knocked off) and the rest focus on DPS (some might have issues with the add spawn, if you wipe on the add, try focusing the dps towards them as a priority and then continue on the demon).\
\
I know many of you are highly interested in the 16 slot bag given by this quest - The chain is fairly long and starts in:\
Horde: Fallen Hero (Swamp of Sorrows, questname \"The Disgraced One\")\
Alliance: NPC in Nethergarde Keep (Blasted Lands - sends you to Fallen Hero)\
\
Chain:\
1.The Disgraced One (Given by Fallen Hero)\
2.The Missing Orders\
3.The Swamp Talker\
4.The Stones That Bind Us (Given by Fallen Hero)\
5.Heroes of Old\
6.Heroes of Old (Reward: Shard of Afrasa)\
7.Kirith (level 55 elite. Given by Fallen Hero)\
8.The Cover of Darkness\
9.The Demon Hunter (Loramus is at 61,66)\
10.Loramus\
11.Breaking the Ward\
12.The Name of the Beast (Talk to Lord Arkkoroc. He is inside the Temple at 76,42)\
13.The Name of the Beast (Kill Hetaera)\
14.The Name of the Beast (Go back to Loramus)\
15.Azsharite\
16.The Formation of Felbane (Galvan is in Stanglethorn)\
17.Enchanted Azsharite Fel Weaponry\
18.Return to the Blasted Lands\
19.Uniting the Shattered Amulet (Kill Sevine, Grol and Allistarj using weapon given by Galvan)\
20.You Are Rakh'likh, Demon (Rakh'likh can be found around 47,23 Blasted Lands)\
\
- Merowlin",
    "3628166769301667692007/10/12 16:14:31MorboRazelikh can be kited all the way to Stonard for those looking to solo this quest.  While immune to all snare/slowing effects a simple speed enchantment or arathi basin foot armor reward will prevent him from gaining ground. \
\
\
The Descent:\
\
The mountain can be safely descended on the northside. The first jump down, to the rune of return plateau, will be the only one to cause damage. Once there drink a potion to recover the lost health and tag Razelikh to maintain the kite. \
\
From the rune of return plateau move to northern most edge. Avoid the rune itself or you will be teleported to the entrance of the tainted scar. You will be able to spot the next highest ledge, and land there by walking backwards off the plateau. Directly east of the ledge will be the obvious safe route down to the road. Be sure to tag Razelikh immediately after making the third jump. \
\
\
The Kite:\
\
Once at the base of the mountain the kite is fairly straight forward. Razelikh's only ranged attack mana burn is the best time to tag him. It is slow casting enough to tag and get out of range. \
\
Illifar so long as not damaged/tagged will bug out at the zone change between Blasted Lands and Swamp of Sorrows. He will simply stand at the arch, but will aggro if you come into range. \
\
\
Stonard:\
\
Stonard's west entrance has 4 Stonard Grunts level 65. Two at the gate, and two patrolling both bunkers.  Simply circle the north bunker until the guards have Razelikh's attention. These will more than enough to finish the boss.\
\
However when Felcular spawns he will go straight for you. Retreat into Stonard itself and run past the blacksmith on the northside of the camp to the northwest gate. There two more grunts will finish him off quickly. Be sure to tag him once so you can loot him. \
\
Level 63 Hunter using defiler's chain greaves without aspect of the cheetah used this method successfully, patch 2.2. Kept pet on Razelikh with growl disabled tagging during mana burn casts with distracting shot rank 6.\
\
Good luck and happy hunting.",
    "3628102031301020312007/06/10 17:17:31audaxThe Usher that summons you to the top of the mountain is located at 48, 23.",
    "3628165678201656782007/10/10 18:00:59regarrThis quest gives you 9950 XP (on a level 51) - quest done with level 51 mage and level 70 feral druid",
    "3628215625021562006/10/23 00:39:27faykanIt should be noted that you get all of these quest rewards; you don't have to pick just one.",
    "362814147210141472006/12/12 13:11:18kreghxJust took this guy down tonight with a 5 man group. He was pretty hard but not as hard as some people are saying. \
\
Group composition - Me - 60 Warrior (prot spec), priest (shadow spec), warlock (using imp), mage, druid. Between us we had about 6 epics - all in pre-MC and in most cases pre-Tier 0 set gear. \
\
So, how did we do it?: \
\
1) Preparation. All casters had a couple of mana pots, health pots. Priest was SS'd, warrior and druid healthstoned. I used dense sharpening stone, strength, agility, spirit scrolls, elixir of superior defense and the usual priest and druid buffs. My gear is reasonable for a non-MC warrior, 5k health unbuffed. \
\
2) Tactics. Summon Raz, warrior taunt him off whoever he goes for, everyone jumps down the hillside to the rune together, taking care to heal once down as the drop can take health off. Warrior tank him with back to hillside so that when he performs his knockback you don't get smacked off the side. \
\
3) Weaken. Use Fel Salve at the start of the fight as you wont get time once his adds pop up. We got the warlock to do it as his spells weren't doing much damage. \
\
4) DPS. Warrior sunders to 5, and everyone lays into him. Mage using arcane missiles, warlock shadowbolt, druid and warrior hitting with large pointy things. \
\
5) Add 1. At 50-60%, Ilifar turned up, and the druid tanked him in bear form while the lock and mage brought him down. I got hit with a knockback here but with my back to the wall I just bounced off and didn't get hurt. Taunt Raz back onto warrior again and continued. \
\
6) DPS 2. With Ilifar dead, I'd tank dps'd Raz down to about 45% in the meantime. We carried on with DPS til he got to around 20%. (Had to re sunder around this point.) \
\
7) Add 2. At this time, Felcular appeared. We got the druid to tank him and self heal while the rest of us continued to smack Raz. Mana was low here, the priest had all but run out, so I whacked on shield wall, healthstoned, and bought the priest some mana up time. 10% \
\
8) Finish him!. Our druid died then, but we'd held them off long enough. Execute along with the support dps finished Raz off, and I dragged Felcular off our warlock. With only one target left, he quickly went down. \
\
9) Victory! ;)",
    "36288011730801172007/05/09 01:26:39BlindcrowOkay to clear up something:  He is not immune to \"all magic\" or at least not as far as I can tell.  He IS immune to shadow, fire, fear, and banish (so as a warlock.. I was freaking useless)  arcane magic DOES seem to work on him though.\
