  ["Uniting the Shattered Amulet60"] = {
    "362716053npcFallen Hero of the Horde7572npcFallen Hero of the Horde757283001362123625336264362753628",
    "36271656110165612006/12/17 13:57:30kreghxWe went with a pretty well equipped group of 2 mages and 1 paladin. First did allistarj. He was relatively easy and we just spammed arcane missiles and he died relatively quick. Note: All bosses are immune for all magic except for arcane and melee and if you dont use the weapon you got prior to this mission, you can't get him lower then 1%. \
Sevine was a LOT harder though. Since the tank was a paladin aggro was lost relatively quick even though we had salvation on us. After wiping twice we just ignored the infernals she calls down and focused on nuking her. We had to push everything we had, potions, mana cookies, shields, cold snap, ice block, etc. But after 3 wipes or so we prevailed. \
The last boss the ogre in Dreadmaul hold was just insane. The worthless lvl 47 adds around him are easily pulled and swat down, but he himself hit incredibly hard. Without a dedicated tank and healer this had no chance and we called it a night.",
    "3627197641101976412007/12/07 21:01:08IttosaiWhen your group is killing Allistarj  if you have a paladin in your group, every time you use the weapon he can strike with hammer of wrath even if Allistarj  still has 100% HP. it also seems to break his cast, but cant say for sure.\
\
Just soloed as a 63 protection paly, Lady Sevine was quite hard, had to use lay on hands, but her Infernals kind of helped the dps, my reckoning was active all the way.",
    "36278679721196962007/05/21 11:04:46BigozLink for the item that replaces the weapon. I don't use daggers, staves, or swords so this came in handy.\
\
http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11582",
    "36271969670196962007/01/07 14:40:28berdanYou don't need to use the weapons given to you in previous steps to fight these bosses. Just talk to the Fallen Hero of the Horde and tell him you've lost the weapons and you'll be given some Fel Salve that works just as well. Saves you from gimping yourself by changing to inferior weapons.\
\
More information regarding this exists in the Enchanted Azsharite Fel Weaponry step of this series: http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3625",
    "36271495271201495272007/09/05 17:43:58kharzakhadThe NPC giving you an enchanted weapon to use against demons from this quest says something like: \"you can use it only once per three minutes\" - we evaluated it to be not true today. You can spam the weapon's use effect nearly continuously.\
\
Effects the weapon has on bosses (when used):\
[ul][li][b]Grol[/b] - it shrinks him, making his attacks WAY weaker. As a level 60 druid in bear form i had no chance to survive without using the weapon. Remember to use the weapon as soon as you see him grow back.[/li]\
[li][b]Lady Sevine[/b] - after few tries we discovered that using a weapon can interrupt her summoning of infernals. We were duoing it with a rogue as dps, and me - druid tanking, so only a rogue get to use her weapon and wasn't as effective as two people could be when it comes to interrupts, but it reduced the number of mobs hitting us.[/li]\
[li][b]Allistarj[/b] - we used a weapon on him of course, but I cannot say what it really did. We had no problems with downing him, and I believe each group (even group of two ;) ) doing this quest won't have problems here.[/li][/ul]\
\
Sidenote: we also tried using the weapons effect on Rakh'likh. I noticed the graphical effect same as the three previous demons, but again cannot say for sure what it really did. I guess it doesn't hurt to use it on him too, anyway.\
\
I hope my comment will be helpful to all people out there doing the old pre-TBC lvl 60 quets ;)",
    "3627212493102124932008/01/03 22:22:36js3bSolo'ed all three as a 67 enhancement shammy. Lady Sevine was the tough one. So many infernals. I was saved by my earth elemental.",
