  ["Against Lord Shalzaru45"] = {
    "287014540npcLatronicus Moonspear7877npcLatronicus Moonspear78772900Darnassus15013130228693287042871",
    "28707486220748622007/04/29 10:25:13tockettIf you are careful and pull from the side, you can grab him and just one of his guards.  I was able to sheep the guard closest to me, and only Shalzaru was pulled.  Be careful though - the mobs around him spawn ridiculously fast.  Just drinking my water to replenish mana sometimes brought new spawns down on me.",
    "28708438910843892007/05/17 04:53:38NeonGenesislvl45 hunter with lvl44 pet: All mobs were pulled without \"social\" agro.\
Also the guards and the Shalzaru shouldn't socially agro if you pull them at the right moment (when the guard and Shalzaru have the most distance between eachother) regardless of what level you are when doing it.\
\
In the water next to the Shalzaru there's an underwater cave, but the only thing I found there were 4 mobs and a mine (Mithril).\
If you decide to venture into there, then be aware that by the time you come out, all mobs from the beginning of the cave up until the water have respawned.  As said above: The respawnrate is quite fast.",
    "2870211996102119962008/01/03 03:42:01z32o[quote=By regarr on 12/15/2006]He is located in in a cave on the island south of Feathermoon Stronghold at 28,71.[/quote]\
\
For the Protection Paladins out there:\
\
I've soloed this quest at level 47, and I found it pretty easy, but rather slow, because you just can't run in aggroing all mobs, most of them are naga sorceress that use Frost Magic and even with your [/i]Frost Resistante Aura (Rank 2)[/i] you won't be able to take less than 100 dmg per cast, lucky then tend to stab you with their stick sometimes.\
\
The second problem is that when these naga are at 15% or lower health, they will run, aggroing other mobs, so I guess you realized you'll be using the [/i]Judgement of Justice[/i] all the time, for preventing them to run. I would recommend using [/i]Hammer of Wrath[/i] when they run, but the mobs here are pretty close to each other, so it would be dangerous.\
\
After you enter the cave, have some things in mind:\
[ul]\
[li]The mobs are real close to each other.[/li]\
[li]75% of the mobs inside are casters.[/li]\
[li]The mobs respawn really fast[/li]\
[li][b][IMPORTANT][/b] Remember that casters can't attack you if you aren't in their line of sight. This cave has decent corners and pillars to hide behind, so that they must chase you, instead of you needing to get to them, which would be dangerous, because you would aggro more mobs.[/li]\
[/ul]\
\
So here is a typical strategy for fighting your way to Lord Shalzaru:\
[ol]\
[li]Load up [i]Seal of Justice[/i][/li]\
[li]Aggro mob and make it come to you[/li]\
[li]Use [i]Judgement[/i][/li]\
[li]Load up [i]Seal of Light[/i][/li]\
[li]Repeat[/li]\
[/ol]\
\
After you reach the dead end of the cave, you will notice that the mobs you killed all the way along are already respawning. As you look to Lord Shalzaru, he will be protected by 2 casters. Please, notice the column of stone on their right side, make your way up to behind that column and wait for the right moment to aggro the caster mob that protects Lord Shalzaru, it will begin to cast [i]Frostbolt[/i], then hide behind the stone column, she will follow you, without aggroing Lord Shalzaru. After you kill this caster mob, it will be easy, as Lord Shalzaru himself uses more melee than spells. Just aggro and kill him, don't forget to take the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=9248][Mysterious Relic][/url] that he drops (because this quest isn't about killing him, it's about recovering that relic.\
\
[b]note:[/b] if you are a miner that can harvest Mithril, the veins respawn very quickly. While I was inside the cave I got 5 points up in Mining from only 2 harvest points.\
\
Rewards:\
4150 XP and 150 Rep with Darnassus\
Also unlocks [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=2871]Delivering The Relic[/url], which consist of talking to a NPC (on the same building where Latronicus Moonspear is) and you will receive more 5550 XP and 250 Rep with Darnassus.",
    "287016065100160652006/12/15 18:42:12regarrHe is located in in a cave on the island south of Feathermoon Stronghold at 28,71. He is a level 47 non-elite with two guards.",
    "2870198536101985362007/12/09 12:57:00contheradsolo'd 46 arms warrior, died once.  definitely come in from the side aggro'd both casters and Lord if ya go in the middle.",
    "287020522211843892007/12/21 18:51:59darth603Looks like the cave might've been his original hiding place back in beta, but I can't say for sure. Its not the kind of place I'd want to go without some kind of water breathing- its really really deep.\
\
Unless some kind of rare spawns in there?\
\
Edit: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=5343]Sure enough...[/url]",
    "2870145592101455922007/08/28 16:58:25ubwcgmBe aware that he runs at low health.",
    "28707997521769232007/05/08 18:16:26NaenthosI experienced the same. With my mage I sheeped one of the guards to see if I got the attention from Lord Shalzaru.. but no. Then, after slaying that guard, I did the same with the other guard.\
