    "522154009054002006/12/02 19:49:05xample22If you are looking for rep with the Agent Dawn, the cauldron quests are the best bet outside of the Undead instances (SC/UD Strath and Scholomance). \
\
Make sure you have your Vitrous Focuser in the bag, if you dont have one you can buy it from the AD Alchemist in Chillwind Camp. Also be sure to equip your AD Commendation trinket. (Save all the scourgestones for when you hit revered). \
\
If you are 60 the best place to go grind  is The Ruins of Andorhal, I can get about 50 Somatic Intensifiers and 3 stacks of Runecloth in an hour worth of grinding as a Rogue, if you are a caster it may be a bit less due to downtime. For a lower level your best bet is going to Dalson's Tears itself. (Always remember that the trick of grinding is killing mobs that you can finish off in 20 seconds or less and that respawn fast). \
\
When you have a good amount of Runecloth and Somatic Intensifiers head to Chillwind Camp and buy some Arcane Quickeners from the AD Alchemist (Those are expensive and if you dont use them fast they will despawn from your bags, so only buy what you need). Return to Dalson's Tears and use the cauldron to deliver the quest. \
\
Then Rinse and repeat. Each turn in will give you about 25 rep for non-humans and about 28 rep for humans.",
