    "41251051360105132006/12/08 04:29:32GokuuSonAlthough there are many elementals and elite giants around, this quest can be easily completed, as you can avoid most danger by riding close to the mountainside, and then with good timing, ride right up to the wreckage and quickly click and complete the quest. When you see the wreckage, it will have a gear over it to click, but that doesn't mean that it'll take a casting time to open, it's an instant click, so even if you manage to attract some unfriendly customers, you can quickly grab the completion and then try to run for it. Happy trails! :)",
    "41255416030541602007/03/20 08:37:01zkittyzThe coords are correct, but depending on your color settings it may be hard to find. Hug the hills all the way to 45* head directly to the shoreline and stand in the water about ankle deep, mouse over the water ,,, Viola",
    "41258700540870052007/05/21 17:29:14Zebrasauceits not a random spawn it always spawns at the same place but its kinda hard to see even if ur right next to it",
    "41251977940197792007/01/08 05:56:06AmberleyEven tho it seems to be a random spawn along the coast, I assume  a few things will remain the same:\
\
The boat is just underwater very close to the shore. Its not breaking thru the surface of the water, thus one would have to look very carefully to spot it.\
\
Wooden boxes seem to be littered around the wreckage aswell. These appear above the water line this might make it somewhat easier to spot the location",
    "4125159410111497252007/09/27 12:50:50VersadesFor those of you who do not have coordinates, the best hint is to look for wreckage along the shore of the main land across from the Isle of Dread (i.e.  southeast of Feathermoon Stronghold almost on a 45 degree angle).  Proceed quite a ways south of the inlet along the mountains, as mentioned above, until you find wreckage on the beach.  It is in a very small cove.\
\
Or, if you prefer, proceed to swim, at a 45 degree angle across the Strait.  This is deep water and you will get Fatigue.  I just managed this in druid aquatic form, can also be done with potions.  I have done it with my human rogue.  So stock water breathing and swim speed if you want to play around with this idea.\
\
The boat is upside down and completely submerged, but it is no longer below the sand.  (Once upon a time all you could see was the rudder, now the entire hull is exposed)  So there is a large clickable spot, and you can see it clearly as a boat.  There is no mistaking this once you see it.\
\
However, the water is highly reflective and that is what keeps you from recognizing the boat itself when you are on the land.  So once you are in the area and see the wreckage, scan the waterline until your cursor turns into the gear.\
\
Soloed as (44) balance druid and (40+) Rogue mobs are a pain.  All 48-49 the giants are elite as mentioned above.",
    "4125181542111497252007/11/09 13:08:50exsanguinatorI just finished this quest and on the beach right next to the boat is a crate. The crate is easy to see though partially submerged. The boat itself is nearly impossible to see under the water unless you already know where it is.",
