    "5201337020033702006/11/10 14:14:50glassthorneOnce this particular quest becomes available, you can use it to your advantage to kill two birds with one stone.\
\
Before you start killing the Winterfall Furbolgs, make certain you have done the Winterfall Activity quest.  (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8464)  Once you complete the quest, you will then be able to collect Winterfall Spirit Beads (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=21383) for the Beads for Salfa quest (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8469).  \
\
This way, you shall be able to grind not only Wintersaber Trainer faction, but you can also grind Timbermaw faction as well with the bead turn-ins.\
\
On a seperate note, if you are getting frustrated by the presence of people in or around the Winterfall camp, if they are of the same faction as yourself, try and see if you can get together in a single party.  Unlike the meat drops, since you are farming for kill counts here, so long as as you are not in a raid every kill will count to the whole group.\
\
However, if they are of the opposite faction there is one (maybe two) things you could do.  First, you could either put up with them and try to tag mobs before they do.  The second bit is a bit more evil and requires a lot of patience to get the ability to do this.\
\
Just ignore the fact that it lists this as Horde only, this quest is available to both factions once they hit exalted with Timbermaw.  It's called The Root of All Evil (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8481).  It gives you a torch that you can use to summon an elite demon to that cave north of the Winterfall Village.  The demon will then try and lay waste to anyone who is unlucky enough to get close to it.  He'll make short work of most farmers, but (and I'm not completely certain on this) until you complete, drop, or fail the quest itself (or maybe log out or leave the area?), he won't despawn.",
    "5201178093311780102007/11/02 11:13:40TamikaThis quest indeed gives 250 reputation on PTR!\
Also I noticed that High Chief Winterfall is now a 58-59 non-elite, gives only 4 Timbermaw Hold reputation (instead of 10 pre-patch), has only 1 guard (nerf to lowbie quest, also more difficult to get rep for wintersaber now, but not much though), 3 times I killed High Chief his guard was a Shaman, but not sure if he's always chammy or just a coincidence, like patrolling chammies/den watchers on the top and down the village.\
Many people may think that waiting for patch to do this grind is quite wise thing to do, but I think that many people will think te same way and several weeks after patch the village will be swarmed all the time, so if waiting for mobs to spawn annoys and you're already revered or close to, do not wait for patch.",
    "5201178010201780102007/11/02 06:50:04dukelukemOn the 2.3 PTR this quest now gives 250 rep",
    "5201497410049742006/11/28 10:42:20ennuiThough there is another quest to kill giants once you're honored with the Wintersaber faction, this quest is your meat and potatoes on this terrible grind.  One thing to take note of: shamans are the rare spawns on this quest.  If i'm the only one farming the village (late late night :P) I try to keep the bottom and middle floor clear of denwatchers and ursas so that shamans have room to spawn.  If you ride up the mountain overlooking the village, there is a whole ridge of Ursas, so you need to maintain a supply of shamans to keep the pace up.\
\
There are 2 patrols that can spawn as shamans as well, on top of the ridge and in front of the village.  If they aren't a shaman, they are a denwatcher, so just take it out and hope for a shaman spawn next time you come back from turning in.\
\
The runners that come through the village do not aggro by proximity but they are social atleast to the chief, so be careful.\
\
There are chests that spawn at both the houses on the edges of the upperlevel, and both the houses at the edge of the bottom level.  I've pulled greens, blues, etc out of them, but usually get ores, bars, food, herbs, water, etc :P  Some of the grinders I quested with completely ignored the chests to save time doing the quest; whatever floats your boat eh? : )\
\
There is a named rare spawn thats also a good snag for greens; he spawns near the chief: http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=10199\
\
When running back to the Quest NPC to turn this quest in, you want to have all your riding speed gear on and basically make a bee-line over the mountain ridges, avoiding mobs because they will knock you off your mount.\
\
You can eventually get very fast at this quest, especially if you can maintain a spawn of shamans up.  Grouping with people, whether or not they are doing the quest, can help a lot as well.\
\
There used to be a bug where you would get credit for quest kills halfway across the map of winterspring, but that was fixed quite some time ago : P",
