    "770110176611962912007/06/10 08:14:43FrankSoloed this guy as a 48 frost mage, sheeped him, kited and killed his adds, got out of combat, went back to him, kited him for a very long time, used a couple of mana pots and bandages and he eventually died. I cleared most of the area from normal mobs before i pulled him as they could have easily been aggroed while i was kiting.",
    "7701137093101370932007/08/13 11:58:40KazumaSolod this on my lvl 48 Affliction Warlock.\
\
The guards don't respawn until you kill the Overseer, so you can kill one, get out of combat (you can jump down at the right onto a platform where they can't reach) and go back up and kill another so you're left alone with the Overseer.\
\
First guard I took down by drain tanking it, while fearing the other guard and seducing the overseer. Second guard the same, and after that I just feared and dotted the overseer to death (make sure you clear the room in front of it so you don't get adds).",
    "77019629130962912007/06/03 01:57:40StrickerAs a Priest at level 51, I simply mind controlled the overseer and let his guard slap him around for 1 minute. When mind control faded, the overseer had 4% health left, so I simply feared, killed the overseer, looted the plans and ran away.",
