    "735196626201966262007/12/05 19:14:25mpoy70Don't bother with this quest! It's not worth the trouble.  The troll boss is almost impossible to solo because of the adds. I couldn't solo the troll boss even when I was lvl49. The ogre and the giant are easier though. Overall is not worth the time and effort.  Avoid this quest.",
    "735171368201713682007/10/18 20:45:56SharkBaitI've done the quest twice and its been about an hours worth of killing murlocks both times for the kelp to drop from the oracles.",
    "73518355241154292007/11/13 15:40:46K21NovaTrivia: \"Dagun\" in this case is a reference to H.P. Lovecraft's Cthulhu mythology, and namely the creature called \"Dagon\".\
\
Check \"The Shadow Over Innsmouth\", a novella by H.P. Lovecraft, for more details. Also, you can find the same story in the game \"The Call of Cthulhu: Dark Corners of the Earth\".",
    "735116190501161902007/07/05 20:26:28hdarkoneThe alter for The hand of Dagun is located at 59,9 in dustwallow marsh",
    "73515429370154292006/12/14 08:35:52skyoverheavenThe Star of Xil'yeh comes from Grel'borg the Miser (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=2417), a named Ogre that patrols around the Alterac Mountains (where all the higher level elite 37-40 ogres are -- you can find him walking from the \"town hall\" type building to the \"castle\" building. Several quests involve killing Grel'borg, so don't be surprised to find other people also hunting him down at the same time.\
\
The Hand of Dagun comes from Dagun the Ravenous (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=2937), a named water giant that is summoned on an island to the north of Theramore. You will know it's the right island when you see a small glowy orb on an altar. To summon Dagun, you need to kill the Mirefin Oracles for a quest item called \"Enchanted Sea Kelp\" -- it only drops from the oracles and may take a while (it's always taken me at least ten minutes of killing to get it on all of my alts). Once you have the  Sea Kelp, you click on the altar and Dagun will rise up from the sea.\
\
Finally, the Legacy Heart comes from Mogh the Undying (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=1060), a named troll in central Stranglethorn Vale (you can find him in some ruins directly south of the Mosh'Ogg Ogre Mound). I believe that he is the hardest to finish (unless in a group) since he's surrounded by many mobs that also respawn fairly quickly. Either bring a friend or two or be 44+, because it's pretty hellish clearing when you're underlevel and soloing.",
    "73512700841154292007/07/26 06:35:50ophirMogh is definitely the most difficult.  He has a human minion who will heal him.  Best advice is to go as a group, but if you want to try him solo, clear the area as much and as quickly as possible.  Respawn rates for these trolls are insane.  You should be able to clear the area down to Mogh, his minion, and maybe one other troll, probably the Headhunter closest to him.  You can try a couple strategies, one of which is to target Mogh and bring him down fast.  Or you can try killing the minion first if it seems like he is healing Mogh faster than you can burn him down.  If I recall, I concentrated on killing Mogh, though.  After all, he is the object of the quest, and he's tough.",
    "73512737041154292007/07/26 20:10:23wvaughn78109Coords are 47.4, 44.7 for Mogh the Undying",
    "735161861101618612007/10/02 13:51:47munkeymanThe two things with this quest that make it difficult is that the drop rate of the oracles is incredibly low. I spent 20 minutes killing them over and over before the kelp finally dropped. \
\
The other thing is that Mogh is surrounded by mobs that i had to pick off one by one until it was down to Mogh, his minion and another headhunter that I couldn't get close enough to kill on his own. Once it was down to those three, I went into Cat form, pounced his little boy and killed him first. With him out of the way, you don't have to worry about Mogh getting healed mid-battle. After that i was able to kill the mob, heal, and then take down Mogh.\
\
grel-Borg is easy, since there are open spots where you can take him w/o worrying about other ogres to jump in.",
    "735137199101371992007/08/13 14:28:02FelkinI used another tactic with my 46 Demonology warlock.\
\
First is the same as what others said, kill all the close trolls.\
After that, I let my VW attack his add, the little boy. I only attacked Mogh, curses and SB, then Shadow Ward and Drain Life until he's dead. The boy vanishes after Mogh dies. He only got healed once.",
