    "450730130121200262007/02/03 15:37:13tholexLeads to: Calm Before the Storm, Alliance ver -> (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4508) Horde -> (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4509)\
\
Be careful, if you're a slow-killing class such as a prot paladin aoeing the mobs, there may be respawns. Be sure to have pots and such ready in case things go bad.\
\
Going out into the hallway is a good idea, but be aware of any potential adds, as the space is small.\
\
Soloed it by a 52 paladin (prot aoe), but had to fight 4, maybe even 5 mobs at a time, 12 mobs in a row... not a very fun fight, used shield / bandage and Lay on Hands. I don't think any other class/spec aside from a mage or a Felguard lock can do this quest before 54.",
    "450795735141933642007/06/02 01:24:09gummAYIf you die (and lose the lure), simply fly back to Gadgetzan, abandon the quest and talk to the alchemist again to get a new one.",
    "450720026280200262007/01/10 13:20:00sturnThe hive is located in the south central region of Un'Goro.  There's only one entrance, which is clearly visible on the map.  When you enter the cave, just keep right, with the exception of a few little niches that are obviously not the correct route.  You'll wind up at a small room that contains the crystal mentioned in the quest text.\
\
When you use the lure, you'll face three waves of enemies: 2 guards, then 3 guards, then 2 guards and queen.  If you lure them out into the hallway, you can rest between waves.  Good luck!\
\
By the way, the Alien Ecology quest (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3883) can be completed in the same room.",
    "4507210057102100572007/12/30 19:10:48platinBe careful if you cannot cure disease, because you can get a nasty debuff that increases physical damage you take by even 40% for 30 minutes ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=8137]Silithid Pox[/url]).\
Also try not to loot the creatures that you kill when cleaning the room and the tunnel. It makes it longer for them to respawn and you really don't like any adds when fighting the queen.",
    "4507172965201729652007/10/22 03:31:26mekrithIf you die, you may not have lost.  The Queen will stay active for awhile (if you got to the third wave); I ran back and nuked her down and then died again to her guards, as a mage.",
    "45072932390293232007/02/02 06:55:58tholexYou must complete Bungle in the Jungle (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4496) to get this quest.",
    "45077049020704902007/04/21 12:28:42koperI made it as 54 retribution pala. Just run into hallway and resting between waves. When there was time for a queen, mobs respawned, when i tryed to pull only one then queen with guards and all mobs there came to me. I focus just on queen, had to use Lay of Hands and Divine Shield + healing, but i made it, i killed queen, rest of mobs killed me. Then just ran there as a ghost and picked up her brain. Hard quest even when is green i guess.",
    "4507177440101774402007/10/31 19:32:35NIghtshadeAlso worth noting that if you are in the tunnel you can't pull just one mob, it seems to be all at once. I pulled the queen, adds followed killed here and then looted before killing adds and the system bugged on me couldn't touch them was down to 20 health still losing 120s and not dying. So be prepared if you loot mid fight for some iritation. Eventually died, and as I had brain rezed in Graveyard and hs back. - Stronly recommend you change HS to Gadget if it is not already.",
    "45079336410933642007/05/30 01:44:45NystiaIt's worth pointing out that if you take your time luring them out into the hall, the queen can despawn, and you don't get the lure back. Make sure you don't take too long to get to the queen once she appears.",
    "4507187830301878302007/11/19 17:26:35zoltyFYI, this quest is both a reference to the game of Chess and the book / movie Starship Troopers.  In which a low level soldier captures a large brain bug.",
    "4507205875111991642007/12/23 04:00:01iMoogleI lost against the second wave as a 56 shadow priest, but I ended up respawning, killing the queen and taking her brain before the mobs killed me. Very difficult to solo, but if you don't mind dying, this is probably the easiest way to complete the quest. Good luck!",
    "4507193779201937792007/11/30 06:09:21NajilOk this quest isn't solo-able ...I suggest you do the quest with 2 more people...at least one of them should be healer.If you stay in the room where there's the crystal you can have no regen time since the waves show up exactly after you kill the last one of each hive...So be prepared for a heavy fight! GL",
    "4507195000101950002007/12/02 17:10:50ShailkkithSolo's this as a 53 rogue with decent weapons. Sword spec. First two waves, I  simply dps'd down and used a major healing pot. I had the disease they give that increases damage taken by 44% after the first wave. so I went into the hallway and used a restorative potion to remove the debuff. Ate. waited for my pot cooldown then pulled the queen into the hallway and got 2 of her adds. Popped all my cooldowns on her, managed to kill one of the adds too, then I vanished. Doable with pots, and knowledge of how to play your class.",
    "45076788961200262007/04/16 00:31:27JohnJSalExcellent idea to lure them in the hallway. You might want to lure the final wave (with the queen) as well, because as soon as I finished killing them, the three regular bugs respawned right around me in the room.",
