    "448346603046602006/11/26 14:06:08SyzgynThis CAN be enchanted through the trade window. Rogues and Druids can stealth run the BRD coffer for the Burning Essence, and give it to anyone once they turn in the quest for the arcanum.",
    "448367912067912006/12/05 22:18:03clyemnestealth running the instance isnt all that simple though, the dogs can see through stealth from a decent distance and taking some of the groups of mobs can be challenging even for a well geared player. having imp sap is definitely a plus",
    "448369731167912006/12/06 04:18:30JerreeI wish I could stealth run.  But honestly, with a decently geared group, pre T1 the instance is cake and coffer runs can be done in 45minutes to 1hour, easy.  Plus, you get some nice sellables.",
    "44839209521598792007/05/27 23:53:49lokhorThat was awesome ^^\
\
Yeah, as a mage this is pretty easy. You can always go invisible if you pull aggro, too. The ideal FR gear: Amulet of the Torn-heart, Flameheart Bracers, Flameheart / Infernoweave Gloves, Infernoweave Leggings, Infernoweave Boots. Put the +8 FR enchant (Flame Armor Kit) on the gloves and boots and this libram on the pants. It adds up to a total of 230 unbuffed FR (not including mage armor), and you are not totally gimped from replacing too many items.",
    "4483172556201725562007/10/21 06:48:41Vesperwith thanks to Zaber's comments I just did this a couple of times to help out the tanks for the illidan encounter. I would like to add the following:\
- you can have multiple Burning Essence in your bag so you can reset the instance over and over (well untill 5x max per hour) until you have all the needed Burning Essence.\
- you can have multiple Lesser Arcanum of Resilience in your bags aswell (they don't stack though)\
\
I just sent all my Libram's through the mail and went flying back and forth to Redridge to pick them up.\
\
This information below from another site ([url=http://wow.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?witem=11751;page=1;howmany=50#1165864703213263922]source[/url]) helped me out aswell.\
The list of Dark Key holders and where they can be found are: \
Dark Keeper Offgut West Garrison - room with Angerforge \
Dark Keeper Bethek Patrols near Coffer room \
Dark Keeper Vorfalk Grim Guzzler Tavern \
Dark Keeper Zimrel Arena; upper seating area \
Dark Keeper Uggel Top of ramp in Golem Room w/Fineous \
Dark Keeper Pelver Domicile room (storeroom in center) \
\
All but 2 are fairly easy to do. \
Bethek spawns almost instantly outside the Coffer room, so be prepared. \
Vorfalk is surrounded by patrons in the Grim Guzzler. To get to him, you have to pull the patrons around him, 1 by 1, with the Dark Iron Ale. \
Just make sure you kill the patron before they drink it, as it's limited in supply. \
After all that, the Burning Essence is still a 50% drop, so you may need a few attempts before you get it.",
