    "138021002711327502007/12/30 18:17:18KorruptiveI am a lv41 warrior and I solo'd it, best thing to do is have some potions and food ready, and a free slot in your bag, killing the first wave is easy, I am arms spec and I just used whirlwind and cleave for the first two enemies, with about 2/3 of my health left, used a potion to top it up, second wave did the same, and 3rd wave with the boss he walks up slowly so now is a VERY good time to use food you have whilst you are out of combat, hopefully you will have full HP after eating.\
\
Ok so now just focus on the boss, mortal strike, heroic strike etc, don't bother wasting rage using whirlwind, cleave etc as it is unlikely that you will kill the other two at this level (41), you probably could kill them if the potion had cooled down, in my case it had not, hopefully the boss should be dead, when he's down quickly loot him for the quest item and you will probably be near your death as I was, at this time you may want to try finishing them off if you feel you have a chance, you could also try hamstringing them to aid your escape, if all else fails I advise jumping off the cliff as I did so you don't have to run all the way up to retrieve your corpse.",
