    "630104314401043142007/06/14 13:48:55fbg111Just did this with my lvl 45 hunter and a lvl 48 fire mage.  He's slow and has a short melee range, but hits frikkin hard if you get too close.  The key to beating him at lower levels is to kite him around trees b/c he has to run around the trees but you can fire through them, and sometimes you can keep him confused as to which side of the tree to go around.  And don't get hit.\
\
There are two really big trees near him, close to the water.  Cleared out the gorillas first so no adds, turned on Aspect of the Pack so the mage and I could keep ahead of him, fire mage switched to Frostbolt to help keep him slow and for mana efficiency and to keep aggro on me.  Growl disabled on pet so it would just dps and not pull aggro from me.  Then ran loops and figure 8's around the trees for a few minutes, slowly dps'ing him down.  Both the mage and I used a mana pot.  At under 1/5 health, mage hit him with Pyroblast, Fireballs, Fireblast, and he was done.",
    "630185162201851622007/11/15 14:27:38dirtdart50As said before very easy with 2.3 patch, solo'ed with 43 mage, he only hit me once is a 42 non-elite... gives 4800xp for quest reward though=-)",
    "630179424101794242007/11/05 04:37:29KimoshiWas able to solo this as a 45 hunter.\
\
A few posts above, a poster mentions two large trees he figure 8'd around to kill him.\
\
What I ended up doing was just get aggro on myself, send my pet in to attack him(without growl) and just kited him around the larger of the two trees w/ aspect of the pack. If you manage to get a decent bit ahead of him around said tree, he'll actually turn around and head to you that way. If you're smart, you can abuse this a few times, make him go back and forth, before having to do a few more rounds.\
\
All I did really was put serpent sting on him, get a bit inhead, and do an auto shot. Run ahead more, another autoshot, rinse, repeat, and reapply Serpent when it's about to fall off.\
\
He also does a small AoE that will probably hit your pet a few times. It doesn't hurt much, but besure to watch your pet's health and use Mend when needed.\
\
Only had to use 2 greater mana potions. I probably could have done it with none in a few more tries as I used Conq shot and arcane shot several times aswell throughout.",
